commit b7ad48d5b7294fb08a958ed71bfe18e77b8f162e
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 09:06:00 2026 -0400

    refactor(cms)(draft-editor): editDocument + applyImageUpload + publish
    
    Add the three write operations to DraftEditor, each addressed by ContentScope
    and routed through scopeKeys:
    - editDocument: encode current → deepMerge(override) → decode (400 IssueError
      on reject) → re-encode → store at the scope's draft key; returns EncodedDoc.
    - applyImageUpload: rewrite a targeted …key field on the draft (raw-bytes
      upload + content-type gate stay in the route).
    - publish: promote the scope's current edit source to the published key, drop
      the draft best-effort, bust the public read cache; 502 IssueError on a
      storage failure.
    
    A decoded document always re-encodes, so encode-after-decode dies rather than
    masquerading as an IssueError. defaultLayer pre-provides ONE shared Storage so
    publish's bust hits the cache the public read serves from.
    
    Route still calls the old inline pipeline; behavior identical (migrated in
    1.3). Tests prove merge preserves unedited deep fields, the present-but-empty
    required field rejects, image-key rewrite persists, and publish goes live on
    the next read.

